							<div class="post">Usually with that many LED&#039;s you would use a matrix display where each row is lit in turn.&nbsp; The problem with this is that if you have 16 rows (and 64 columns) each row can only be lit 1/16th of the time, limiting brightness.&nbsp; If you want maximum brightness you will need a fixed current power supply and a transistor switch for EACH of the 1000 LEDs.&nbsp; This can run into a lot of money.</div>
